$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Did the arbiter arrive yet?

Tingko: Yes, I saw her enter the hall along with the chieftains.
Princess... do you really want to do this?
Tindoiimu: Sophie and them have been locked up for days now. They're scared, and unsafe...
Tindoiimu: I've been waiting for her to arrive. I can't pass up this chance, now.
Tingko: I know you're worried about them, but I'm more worried about you.
Tingko: If things get violent with the qilin chieftain...
Tindoiimu: I have proof, Tingko! And I have that jackal's confession!
Tindoiimu: I just need the arbiter to listen...
Tingko: But Princess, you're not supposed to—
Tindoiimu: There's no other way.

Qing-Feng: You're saying that one of my men accepted bribes from some... theater troupe?
Where's you're proof!?
Tindoiimu: These two permits both carry official seals.
Tindoiimu: Do you really think some foreign circus troupe has the means of fabricating such a complicated seal?
Qing-Feng: ......
Tindoiimu: ...Let me put it this way. Why would one of your subordinates stamp a fake permit with an official seal?
Juan-Yun: Father, these two really are both official seals. They even say "Sophie Lee" on top.
Juan-Yun: Even if it was just a mistake, there should be records of it. Why would the bureau issue the same person two of the same permits?
Juan-Yun: What if they really did take a bribe...
Qing-Feng: Shut up! Quit talking nonsense in front of the arbiter!
Maeok: I'm just here to drink tea. This doesn't sound like any of my business.
Maeok: Still, it does seem fishy. There must have been a mistake somewhere along the line.
Tindoiimu: That's also possible, I'm not going to say anything for certain. I just ask that the arbiter at least runs a check on that thief.
Tindoiimu: And since my friends do have the proper certification to hold their circus performances, I ask that they be set free.
Maeok: Qing Feng, you've always been a resonable man...
Maeok: Since all this just seems like an oversight,
Maeok: I assume you'd like to get this sorted out quickly, right?
Juan-Yun: Yeah, those people we've got in prison are innocent!
Qing-Feng: ...The arbiter is right. It was just a small oversight, not something I'd like to ruin my reputation over.
Qing-Feng: Once everything checks out to be as the Insect Princess claims, then they will be set free.
Maeok: Worry not, princess. Qing-Feng is the qilin chieftain, you should take him at his word.
Tindoiimu: Thank you very much, your eminence.
Maeok: Well, it is getting late. If you would excuse me, I still have many things to take care of.
Qing-Feng: ...Then I won't keep you, arbiter. Juan-Yun, please see the arbiter back safely for me.
Juan-Yun: Of course. Please come with me, Arbiter Maeok.
Qing-Feng: Well, Princess, you sure do know how to pick your battles.
Tindoiimu: ...I'm just worried about my friends. I couldn't wait any longer.
Qing-Feng: Ah yes, you've been out and about making all sorts of friends I see...
Qing-Feng: Seems like our tribe will have to consider whether or not we've given you too much freedom.
Tingko: Princess, Qing-Feng looked pretty angry walking out just now. Did you manage to convince him?
Tindoiimu: I did, thanks to the arbiter. At least I've caused the Qilin Tribe to lose a bit of face.
Tingko: Great! I guess now we just wait until Sophie and them are let out, and then we can go see them together!
Tindoiimu: I've been so worried about them these past few days...
Tindoiimu: (But it's fine... they're fine... they'll be let out...)
Tingko: Princess...
Tindoiimu: When they're let out, you go see them for me. And tell this to Sophie for me...
Sophie: Ru-yi, next time we go shopping we'll have to cut back on the necessities, since we didn't earn too much this leg of the tour...
Ru-yi: I know, I know~ Relax, Sophie!
Ru-yi: But we don't have much time left here~
Sophie: Ying even told us, if we want to make enough money to eat and sleep, then we should get out of the east sooner than later...
Ru-yi: I really miss those two...
Ru-yi: We haven't seen them at all since we've been let out...
Sophie: I know, but... But I'm sure that they're the only reason we were let out in the first place.
Ru-yi: Tim and Ying... I guess we'll never really find out their true identities.
Sophie: I guess it's not a big deal, but...
Sophie: I would have liked to see them just one more time before we left, to say thank you.
Ru-yi: Sophie, look! Looks like there's a big sale going on!
Sophie: Eh!? Where!?
Tindoiimu: ......
Sophie: Ow...! Eh? Hey, who's that girl being followed by those guards?
Sale Manager: Guards? Oh, qilin guards, huh~
Sale Manager: That's probably the insect princess.
Sale Manager: She's a qilin hostage right now.
Sophie: Insect princess? Hmm... She looks quite magnificent, from the back at least...
Sophie: (I bet a princess like that would make a great match for Tim...)
Sale Manager: Hey, kid, are you gonna buy something or not!?
Sophie: Maybe I would if you lowered your prices a little! You call this a sale!?
Tingko: Princess, don't you want to say goodbye?
Tindoiimu: No need to say goodbye...
Tindoiimu: Even though I don't think we'll ever see each other again...
Tingko: That's sad, though... She was a friend, and we don't have too many friends.
Tindoiimu: It's good to see she seems healthy, at least. She looks happy.
Tingko: Of course she is. She was always happy~
Tindoiimu: (Keep at it, Sophie. I hope you can travel everywhere you want to go...)
Tindoiimu: (And do it with a smile.)
